          "email": "alexander_boyko@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2015-01-12 10:06:09.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-6112 ldlm: wakeup ldlm waiters when error happened",
        "message": "LU-6112 ldlm: wakeup ldlm waiters when error happened\n\nWhen n process use the same file, and share osc_lock for it,\nthere is situation when one process is sleeping at ldlm_lock_match,\nsecond doing cl_lock_enqueue. Lock request was sent, and process is\nkilled by signal. The second process wakeup from cl_lock_state_wait()\ndetach osc lock from ldlm and fail with -EINPROGRESS. Client recive\ncompletion and grant ldlm lock, but ldlm_handle_cp_callback could not\nwakeup the first process because osc_ldlm_completion_ast() end with\nELDLM_NO_LOCK_DATA because no osc_lock is attached  to ldlm.\nAfter timeout server evict client and client has error:\n  ldlm_resource_complain()): refcount nonzero (1) after lock cleanup;\n\nThis patch adds wakeup at error handle path for ldlm waiters.\n\nSigned-off-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander.boyko@seagate.com>\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-2326\nChange-Id: I60cd1c9a594696c0fbe242fcd0b09b252a8a3b2e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
